au.edu.rmit.tzar.runners

Class JythonRunner

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.rmit.tzar.runners.JythonRunner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runner

    public class JythonRunner
extends java.lang.Object
implements Runner
    A runner which calls out to a Runner implemented in Jython code. The runner must be implemented in a file "modelrunner.py", and the class name must be ModelRunner. Output from the runner will be logged to a file in the output directory.

      • runModel

        public boolean runModel(java.io.File model,
               java.io.File outputPath,
               java.lang.String runId,
               java.lang.String runnerFlags,
               Parameters parameters,
               java.util.logging.Logger logger)
                 throws TzarException
        Description copied from interface: Runner
        Runs the provided model code. "model" points to a local source repository. Implementations of this runner are expected to be able to run code found at this location.
        Specified by:
        runModel in interface Runner
        Parameters:
        model - the path to the model source code or executable
        outputPath - local path for the model to write output data to
        runId - a unique identifier for the run to execute
        runnerFlags - space separated flags for the runner
        logger - a java logger for the runner code to use for logging. This logger will log to a file in the output directory. By default, INFO level logs will go to console. If --verbose is set, then FINE logs will also go to console.
        Returns:
        true if the run succeeded, false otherwise
        Throws:
        TzarException
